# API implementation rules

## Pattern

- Validate all request bodies with a schema.
- Keep provider API calls in `src/lib/xApi.ts` or a dedicated service layer.
- Keep token encryption in `src/lib/tokenCrypto.ts`.
- Use server-side jobs for deletion.
- Do not block HTTP requests on large deletion batches.

## X API deletion

Real deletion must call the official endpoint server-side for each owned post ID. The client can request a job, but the server decides what IDs are valid and deletable.

## Error handling

- Classify errors as validation, auth, rate limit, provider, or unknown.
- Stop jobs on repeated auth errors.
- Back off on provider or rate limit errors.
- Store failure reason per post.

## Testing priorities

- OAuth state validation
- PKCE generation
- Token encryption round trip
- Archive parser allowlist
- Queue hash stability
- Verse validation
- Delete job creation guardrails
